<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 4:28AM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Vance,
northern Warren and northwestern Halifax Counties through 515 AM
EDT...
At 426 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Norlina, or near Warrenton, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph, heavy rainfall and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible. Localized flooding from heavy rainfall is also
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Warrenton, Norlina, Littleton, Middleburg, Macon, Kerr Lake, Wise,
Lake Gaston, Southpointe And Morningstar Marinas and Satterwhite
Point Marina.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
